'''''The Wrath of Magra''''' is a [[role-playing video game]] published by Carnell Software for the [[ZX Spectrum]] in 1984.<ref name='microadventurer6' /> It is a sequel to 1983's ''[[Volcanic Dungeon]]''.<ref>{{cite magazine|author=John Edwards|url=https://spectrumcomputing.co.uk/page.php?issue_id=968&page=98|issue=1 |title=Beware the Wrath of Magra!|page=98|magazine=CRASH|publisher=Newsfield |access-date=2023-05-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://spectrumcomputing.co.uk/page.php?issue_id=319&page=58|page=58|magazine=Your Spectrum|title=Rumbles|publisher=Sportscene Specialist Press |access-date=2023-05-05}}</ref>

The game contents included two program cassettes, a manual, and a 158-page paperback book entitled 'The Book of Shadows' containing stories, a bestiary, spells, and over 50 black and white illustrations.

Carnell went into liquidation soon after publication<ref name='microadventurer10'>{{cite magazine|url=https://archive.org/details/MicroAdventurer10-Aug84/page/n23/mode/2up?view=theater|page=23|magazine=Micro Adventurer|publisher=Sunshine Publications|title=Wrath of the Receiver|issue= 10 |date=August 1984 |access-date=2015-11-03}}</ref> and the game was re-released later in the year by [[Mastertronic]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://spectrumcomputing.co.uk/page.php?issue_id=977&page=40 |magazine=CRASH|issue=10|page=40|date=November 1984|title=Magra Back Again|publisher=Newsfield|access-date=2023-05-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://spectrumcomputing.co.uk/page.php?issue_id=30&page=10 |magazine=Sinclair User|page=10|issue=30|title=News: Carnell Returns From The Grave |date=September 1984 |access-date=2023-05-05 }}</ref>

