==Plot==
In ''[[Volcanic Dungeon]]'', the Knight of Star Jewel rescued the kidnapped Princess Edora and killed her evil captor Magra, the most powerful sorceress in the world. However, Magra has been restored back to life by her followers and wants revenge upon the man who defeated her. She cursed Edora and so the knight needs to once again save the princess. He needs to reach Magra's castle in the Black Mountains and find a way to destroy the witch forever.

==Reception==
''Wrath of Magra'' was generally well received.<ref name='microadventurer10' /> It received review ratings of 30/40 from ''[[Personal Computer Games]]''<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://archive.org/stream/personalcomputergames-magazine-08/PersonalComputerGames_08#page/n91/mode/1up/|page=90|title=The Magic of Magra |magazine=Personal Computer Games Magazine| issue=8 |publisher=VNU|access-date=2023-05-05}}</ref> and 8/10 from ''[[Sinclair User]]''.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://spectrumcomputing.co.uk/page.php?issue_id=31&page=36 |magazine=Sinclair User|issue=31|title=Dungeonmaster Magra |date=October 1984|access-date=2023-05-05}}</ref> ''[[Crash (magazine)|Crash]]'', however, gave it an average score of 5/10,<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://spectrumcomputing.co.uk/page.php?issue_id=977&page=115|page=115|magazine=Crash|title=The Wrath of Magra|issue=10|date=November 1984|publisher=Newsfield|access-date=2023-05-05}}</ref> while ''[[Computer and Video Games]]'' scored it only 3/10.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://spectrumcomputing.co.uk/page.php?issue_id=6952&page=25|page=25|title=The Wrath of Magra|magazine=Computer and Video Games|issue=41|access-date=2023-05-05}}</ref>

D J Robinson reviewed ''The Wrath of Magra'' for ''[[Imagine (AD&D magazine)|Imagine]]'' magazine, and stated that "In conclusion, The Wrath of Magra is an exceptionally good adventure, well written and presented, with a vast amount of atmosphere and the best background material I have ever seen."<ref name="Imagine24">{{cite journal | last = Robinson |first = D J | title =Micro Reviews | type = review | journal = [[Imagine (game magazine)|Imagine]] | issue = 24| pages =39| publisher = TSR Hobbies (UK), Ltd. |date=March 1985}}</ref>

